<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Cityhold 15-month shr falls into loss.</title>
<headline>Cityhold 15-month shr falls into loss.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>15 months ended Dec 31 versus 12 months to Sept 30, 1996</p>
<p>		    (million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib loss (cts)  7.32	  vs 2.65 profit</p>
<p>    Shr, headline loss (cts)1.79	  vs 8.08 profit</p>
<p>    Headline loss	     1.16	  vs 5.15 profit</p>
<p>    Attrib loss		 4.73	  vs 1.69 profit</p>
<p>    Pre-tax loss		2.54	  vs 3.74 profit</p>
<p>    Tax			   2.19	  vs 2.04</p>
<p>    Pre-exceps profit	 1.00	  vs 7.19</p>
<p>    Net finance costs	 7.21	  vs 4.90</p>
<p>    Turnover		  232.92	  vs 182.09</p>
<p>Full name: City Investment Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	 3.57	  vs 3.46</p>
<p>NOTE - The group has changed its financial year end to December 31. The figures reflect the 15 months to end December compared to the previous 12 month period to end September 1996.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
